  "text": "When the quantum set Q is approximated by a superset relaxationQ that admits a semidefinite programming [CITATION_1] characterization, the optimization problem of Eq. (C1) can also be solved as an SDP. To this end, note that the SDP characterization ofQ is achieved in terms of some moment matrix χ that contains all the entries of P as some of its matrix elements.",
